# Genzite System Context

Genzite is an AI-Powered No-Code Business Application Builder & Dynamic CMS.

## Tech Stack
- Backend: NestJS Microservices (TypeScript, 7 independent services)
- Frontend: React + Vite + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS v4
- Database: PostgreSQL (Relational + JSONB) + Redis (Cache + Queue)
- AI: Google Gemini API
- Cloud: AWS (Route 53, CloudFront, S3, ALB, EC2, RDS, ElastiCache)

## Project Structure
- `apps/` — All deployable applications (7 NestJS services + 1 React frontend)
- `packages/` — Shared libraries (shared-types: DTOs, Events, Constants)
- `infra/` — Docker Compose orchestration
- `docs/` — Product spec, DB design, API contracts, architecture docs

## Microservices
- `apps/gateway` (port 3000) — API Gateway, JWT verification, rate limiting
- `apps/identity-service` (port 3001) — Auth, JWT, RBAC
- `apps/site-service` (port 3002) — Sites, Pages, Widgets (Canvas Builder)
- `apps/data-service` (port 3003) — Dynamic CMS Collections & Records (JSONB)
- `apps/media-service` (port 3004) — S3 Presigned URL generation
- `apps/notification-service` (port 3005) — Email, Push, In-App notifications
- `apps/ai-service` (port 3006) — Google Gemini integration (generation + recruitment)

## Critical Architecture Rules
1. Each service has its own database schema. Services NEVER access each other's DB directly.
2. Cross-service communication via Kafka events (async) or API Gateway (sync).
3. Dynamic user data MUST use PostgreSQL JSONB. NEVER create fixed columns for dynamic fields.
4. Media uploads bypass the backend entirely (Presigned URL → S3 direct upload).
5. The AI service must be isolated to avoid blocking core operations (Gemini calls take 10-15s).
6. QA focuses 100% on functional backend API verification. UI testing is STRICTLY EXCLUDED.
7. UI aesthetic must be cozy, user-friendly, and home-oriented. Reject harsh IT-dashboard designs.